
Environmental Justice:
	- Looks at connections and correlations between inequality and environmental 
	  problems
	- Connects histories of racism, colonialism, discrimination, and classism 
	  to disproportional impacts of environmental problems.
	- Asks whether effects are related to minority group status
	- Fair treatment and meaningful involvement of all people with respect to
	  env laws, regulations, policies

Environmental Racism:
	- Geographic relationship between env degredation and low-income/minority
	  communities





The Globalization of Environmental Justice: Lessons from the U.S.-Mexico Border
David V. Carruthers

